{"key":"post-12833268","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>12833268</id>\n<content>Actually, brf jars should be sterilized right away or refrigerated.&amp;nbsp; The damp rice flour can go rancid in a short time.&amp;nbsp; If it's not over 12 hours, you're probably OK, but don't let them go long enough to get stinky.&amp;nbsp; If they smell rancid, toss them out and make a fresh batch.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;It only takes half an hour at most to whip up a batch of brf, so it's always better to do it immediately before loading your sterilizer.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>12833329</next>\n<prev>12833113</prev>\n<first>12832827</first>\n<last>12833367</last>\n<when>1277988693</when>\n<utime>07/01/10 03:51 PM</utime>\n</post>"}